# 
# https://w3id.org/ftr#Benchmark
<https://w3id.org/ftr#Benchmark> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#Benchmark> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Benchmarks are community-specific groupings of a set of Metrics that provides a narrative of those particular ways in which that community defines FAIR for assessment purposes."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#Benchmark> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Benchmark"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ftr#BenchmarkScore
<https://w3id.org/ftr#BenchmarkScore> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#BenchmarkScore> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dqv#QualityMeasurement> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#BenchmarkScore> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Score obtained after executing a scoring algorithm over a set of test results. The benchmark score includes a value, a log and a link to the test results used to obtain the score. "@en .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#BenchmarkScore> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Benchmark score"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ftr#GuidanceContext
<https://w3id.org/ftr#GuidanceContext> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#GuidanceContext> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Class that represents a concrete suggestion from a test. A guidance context has a title, description and points to a general guidance element (e.g., a good practice)"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#GuidanceContext> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Guidance context"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ftr#Metric
<https://w3id.org/ftr#Metric> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#Metric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dqv#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#Metric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Narrative description that a Test must wholly implement. Metrics may be domain-agnostic or not."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#Metric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Metric"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ftr#ScoringAlgorithm
<https://w3id.org/ftr#ScoringAlgorithm> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#ScoringAlgorithm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A benchmark implementation in the form of an interpretative algorithm. \nAlgorithms may specify the exact set of tests which are to be run by the assessment service. Algorithms contextualise the sum of all test results for a given benchmark, into a final quantitative assessment result. The execution of an algorithm yields an assessment result."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#ScoringAlgorithm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Scoring algorithm"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ftr#Test
<https://w3id.org/ftr#Test> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#Test> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#DataService> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#Test> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Agent> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#Test> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Service, formed by an API and associated piece of code that implements a Metric, and is executed (by a FAIR assessment tool), retrieving a particular result."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#Test> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Test"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ftr#TestExecutionActivity
<https://w3id.org/ftr#TestExecutionActivity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#TestExecutionActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Activity> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#TestExecutionActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The action carried out by an agent of calling an API in which a test (or set of tests) were run. The result of this activity is either a `TestResult` or a `TestResultSet`."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#TestExecutionActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Test execution activity"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ftr#TestResult
<https://w3id.org/ftr#TestResult> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#TestResult> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#TestResult> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Output of running a test over a resource. A test result also should contain provenance metadata about the process followed to create it. `TestResult`is represented as an extension of `prov:Entity`. A test result points to the corresponding test specification through the `ftr:definedBy` property." .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#TestResult> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Test result"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ftr#TestResultSet
<https://w3id.org/ftr#TestResultSet> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#TestResultSet> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Collection> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#TestResultSet> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity> .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#TestResultSet> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A set of FAIR test results, together with their respective metadata. Common metadata may describe the set. For example, if all results where run by a request to the same API."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ftr#TestResultSet> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Test result set"@en .
